{"messages": "[{\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": \"You are a helpful AI assistant that uses tools to complete tasks.\"}, {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Review the conversation above and consider saving or updating a skill if appropriate.\\n\\nFocus on: was a non-trivial approach used to complete a task that required trial and error, or changing course due to experiential findings along the way, or did the user expect or desire a different method or outcome?\\n\\nIf a relevant skill already exists, update it with what you learned. Otherwise, create a new skill if the approach is reusable.\\nIf nothing is worth saving, just say 'Nothing to save.' and stop.\"}, {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": \"Let me check what skills exist that might be relevant, then decide what to save.\", \"tool_calls\": [{\"function\": {\"name\": \"skills_list\"}}]}]", "source": "session_20260324_130233_d31067.json", "collected_at": "2026-03-26T12:28:33.937558"}
{"messages": "[{\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": \"You are a helpful AI assistant that uses tools to complete tasks.\"}, {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Review the conversation above and consider saving or updating a skill if appropriate.\\n\\nFocus on: was a non-trivial approach used to complete a task that required trial and error, or changing course due to experiential findings along the way, or did the user expect or desire a different method or outcome?\\n\\nIf a relevant skill already exists, update it with what you learned. Otherwise, create a new skill if the approach is reusable.\\nIf nothing is worth saving, just say 'Nothing to save.' and stop.\"}, {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": \"There are several skills that should be updated or created based on this session. The key reusable approach here was: **auditing a bloated cron system, designing a lean architecture from first principles, and rebuilding with clear job boundaries**. Let me also check which learning/persona skills are now obsolete and should be cleaned up.\", \"tool_calls\": [{\"function\": {\"name\": \"skill_manage\"}}]}]", "source": "session_20260324_130233_d31067.json", "collected_at": "2026-03-26T12:28:33.937582"}
{"messages": "[{\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": \"You are a helpful AI assistant that uses tools to complete tasks.\"}, {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"get the new browser use from git. v2 is crazy people are saying also can i download chrome in here. if we can please do it and show me how to use it. and i want you to be able touse it in the new update theyve made access for agents to use the web\"}, {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": \"The VNC server **IS running**! Let me fix the issues and give you clear instructions.\\n\\n## \\ud83c\\udfaf CURRENT STATUS:\\n\\n\\u2705 **VNC server is running** on port 5901\\n\\u2705 **Xvfb virtual display** is active\\n\\u26a0\\ufe0f Chromium launch script still needs fixes\\n\\u2753 Need to connect VNC client from your computer\\n\\n---\\n\\n## \\ud83d\\udd27 FIX 1: Update the Chromium launch command\\n\\nThe script needs better flags. Let me fix it:\", \"tool_calls\": [{\"function\": {\"name\": \"execute_code\"}}]}]", "source": "session_20260322_181512_dad208.json", "collected_at": "2026-03-26T12:28:33.937611"}
{"messages": "[{\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": \"You are a helpful AI assistant that uses tools to complete tasks.\"}, {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"get the new browser use from git. v2 is crazy people are saying also can i download chrome in here. if we can please do it and show me how to use it. and i want you to be able touse it in the new update theyve made access for agents to use the web\"}, {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": \"Now let's restart VNC with a cleaner configuration:\", \"tool_calls\": [{\"function\": {\"name\": \"execute_code\"}}]}]", "source": "session_20260322_181512_dad208.json", "collected_at": "2026-03-26T12:28:33.937633"}
{"messages": "[{\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": \"You are a helpful AI assistant that uses tools to complete tasks.\"}, {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"alrigth thats not working just use it without a account in it\"}, {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": \"Alright, let's skip the Google account and run browser-use **without authentication**. That's actually simpler and works great for many tasks.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## \\ud83c\\udfaf SIMPLE SETUP - NO GOOGLE ACCOUNT NEEDED\\n\\nWe already have everything installed:\\n- browser-use 0.12.2\\n- Chromium\\n- Ollama + llama3.2\\n\\nLet's create a simple agent that works **headless** (no display) and doesn't need any login:\", \"tool_calls\": [{\"function\": {\"name\": \"execute_code\"}}]}]", "source": "session_20260322_181512_dad208.json", "collected_at": "2026-03-26T12:28:33.937677"}
{"messages": "[{\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": \"You are a helpful AI assistant that uses tools to complete tasks.\"}, {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"alrigth thats not working just use it without a account in it\"}, {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": \"Let's test it now:\", \"tool_calls\": [{\"function\": {\"name\": \"execute_code\"}}]}]", "source": "session_20260322_181512_dad208.json", "collected_at": "2026-03-26T12:28:33.937701"}
{"messages": "[{\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": \"You are a helpful AI assistant that uses tools to complete tasks.\"}, {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Review the conversation above and consider saving or updating a skill if appropriate.\\n\\nFocus on: was a non-trivial approach used to complete a task that required trial and error, or changing course due to experiential findings along the way, or did the user expect or desire a different method or outcome?\\n\\nIf a relevant skill already exists, update it with what you learned. Otherwise, create a new skill if the approach is reusable.\\nIf nothing is worth saving, just say 'Nothing to save.' and stop.\"}, {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": \"**YES - This is absolutely worth saving as a skill.**\\n\\nThe conversation involved:\\n- **Non-trivial trial and error**: Multiple failed approaches (VNC+Google auth, subclassing with Pydantic Field, various wrapper attempts)\\n- **Changing course**: Switched from authenticated browser to headless, discovered the `.provider` and `.model_name` requirement through errors\\n- **User expectation**: Wanted browser-use v2 working without paid APIs/Google auth - we delivered that\\n- **Reusable solution**: The wr\", \"tool_calls\": [{\"function\": {\"name\": \"execute_code\"}}]}]", "source": "session_20260322_181512_dad208.json", "collected_at": "2026-03-26T12:28:33.937724"}
