{"messages": "[{\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": \"You are a helpful AI assistant that uses tools to complete tasks.\"}, {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"we dont wanna use ollama model but a model from browser use itself. this is the model name- bu-30b-a3b-preview\"}, {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": \"Ah! You want to use **browser-use's own model** (not Ollama). Let's check what that is and set it up.\\n\\n## \\ud83d\\udd0d What is `bu-30b-a3b-preview`?\\n\\nThis looks like a **browser-use specific model** - likely hosted on their infrastructure or a custom fine-tune. Let's check browser-use's model configuration:\", \"tool_calls\": [{\"function\": {\"name\": \"execute_code\"}}]}]", "source": "session_20260322_142255_9be873.json", "collected_at": "2026-03-26T12:28:33.943841"}
