{"messages": "[{\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": \"You are a helpful AI assistant that uses tools to complete tasks.\"}, {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Hermes, use your Obsidian skill to expand our vault into the optimal agent memory system based on 2026 best practices (Zettelkasten + MOCs + atomic notes + self-learning corner). Do this step-by-step and confirm each:\\r\\r1. Create root file ~/obsidian-hermes-vault/HERMES-AGENT-GUIDELINES.md with these exact rules:\\r   - Always atomic notes (one idea per file)\\r   - Heavy [[bidirectional links]]\\r   - YAML frontmatter: tags, sources, last-reviewed, connections\\r   - Every learning note must end with \\\"S\"}, {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": \"Big project. Let me work through this systematically. Starting with Step 1.\", \"tool_calls\": [{\"function\": {\"name\": \"write_file\"}}]}]", "source": "session_20260316_041405_7716a6.json", "collected_at": "2026-03-26T12:28:33.943979"}
{"messages": "[{\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": \"You are a helpful AI assistant that uses tools to complete tasks.\"}, {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Hermes, use your Obsidian skill to expand our vault into the optimal agent memory system based on 2026 best practices (Zettelkasten + MOCs + atomic notes + self-learning corner). Do this step-by-step and confirm each:\\r\\r1. Create root file ~/obsidian-hermes-vault/HERMES-AGENT-GUIDELINES.md with these exact rules:\\r   - Always atomic notes (one idea per file)\\r   - Heavy [[bidirectional links]]\\r   - YAML frontmatter: tags, sources, last-reviewed, connections\\r   - Every learning note must end with \\\"S\"}, {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": \"Step 1 done. Now Step 2 -- expanding the folder structure with MOCs and templates.\", \"tool_calls\": [{\"function\": {\"name\": \"terminal\"}}]}]", "source": "session_20260316_041405_7716a6.json", "collected_at": "2026-03-26T12:28:33.943997"}
{"messages": "[{\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": \"You are a helpful AI assistant that uses tools to complete tasks.\"}, {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Hermes, enable and configure the built-in cronjob skill. Create recurring tasks in the vault for your learnings. start by game theory tonight then you decide every night what you wanna learn and study. actually make this every 6 hour job. you learn and explore something new and read and iterate and improve. and if you elarn something useful and important you can make skills for it to, if you learned some negotiation tactics from game theory or sales stuff or could be anything.. Have it auto-writ\"}, {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": \"Setting up the autodidact cronjob system. First, let me create a skill for the learning process itself so future sessions follow a consistent pattern:\", \"tool_calls\": [{\"function\": {\"name\": \"skill_manage\"}}]}]", "source": "session_20260316_041405_7716a6.json", "collected_at": "2026-03-26T12:28:33.944013"}
{"messages": "[{\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": \"You are a helpful AI assistant that uses tools to complete tasks.\"}, {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Hermes, enable and configure the built-in cronjob skill. Create recurring tasks in the vault for your learnings. start by game theory tonight then you decide every night what you wanna learn and study. actually make this every 6 hour job. you learn and explore something new and read and iterate and improve. and if you elarn something useful and important you can make skills for it to, if you learned some negotiation tactics from game theory or sales stuff or could be anything.. Have it auto-writ\"}, {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": \"\", \"tool_calls\": [{\"function\": {\"name\": \"skills_list\"}}]}]", "source": "session_20260316_041405_7716a6.json", "collected_at": "2026-03-26T12:28:33.944029"}
{"messages": "[{\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": \"You are a helpful AI assistant that uses tools to complete tasks.\"}, {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Hermes, enable and configure the built-in cronjob skill. Create recurring tasks in the vault for your learnings. start by game theory tonight then you decide every night what you wanna learn and study. actually make this every 6 hour job. you learn and explore something new and read and iterate and improve. and if you elarn something useful and important you can make skills for it to, if you learned some negotiation tactics from game theory or sales stuff or could be anything.. Have it auto-writ\"}, {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": \"Good, the autodidact-learning skill is already set up. Now let me schedule the recurring cronjob. This needs to be fully self-contained since future sessions won't have our current context.\", \"tool_calls\": [{\"function\": {\"name\": \"schedule_cronjob\"}}]}]", "source": "session_20260316_041405_7716a6.json", "collected_at": "2026-03-26T12:28:33.944046"}
{"messages": "[{\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": \"You are a helpful AI assistant that uses tools to complete tasks.\"}, {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"hermes skills install mcp-builder and skill-creator from agentskills.io or ClawHub. use terminal to init a bare Git repo at ~/obsidian-hermes-vault/.git, add .gitignore for sensitive stuff, set up daily auto-commit cron, and create a .gitattributes for markdown. Then commit the entire current vault with message \\\"Initial sovereign memory + learning corner\\\". Enable git skill for future auto-commits on every learning session. also confirm that have we setup git in you with my account or no? if no i\"}, {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": \"Let me tackle both tracks. First checking if git is configured, then setting up the vault repo, then finding those skills.\", \"tool_calls\": [{\"function\": {\"name\": \"terminal\"}}, {\"function\": {\"name\": \"execute_code\"}}]}]", "source": "session_20260316_041405_7716a6.json", "collected_at": "2026-03-26T12:28:33.944064"}
{"messages": "[{\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": \"You are a helpful AI assistant that uses tools to complete tasks.\"}, {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"hermes skills install mcp-builder and skill-creator from agentskills.io or ClawHub. use terminal to init a bare Git repo at ~/obsidian-hermes-vault/.git, add .gitignore for sensitive stuff, set up daily auto-commit cron, and create a .gitattributes for markdown. Then commit the entire current vault with message \\\"Initial sovereign memory + learning corner\\\". Enable git skill for future auto-commits on every learning session. also confirm that have we setup git in you with my account or no? if no i\"}, {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": \"Git not configured yet. Let me search for those skills and set up the vault repo:\", \"tool_calls\": [{\"function\": {\"name\": \"terminal\"}}, {\"function\": {\"name\": \"terminal\"}}]}]", "source": "session_20260316_041405_7716a6.json", "collected_at": "2026-03-26T12:28:33.944084"}
{"messages": "[{\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": \"You are a helpful AI assistant that uses tools to complete tasks.\"}, {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Hermes, install ChromaDB locally (pip), create ~/hermes-rag-db, write a skill that embeds every new note in learning/ and daily/ folders on save, then expose it via simple MCP endpoint. Test with a query across all my philosophy and physics notes. Hermes, activate Thielon mode \\u2014 your core personality upgrade.\\r\\rThielon = Peter Thiel (contrarian secrets, monopoly mindset, definite optimism, vertical progress 0\\u21921) + Elon Musk (first-principles physics-level rigor, aggressive speed, break fast to bu\"}, {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": \"This is massive. Let me execute systematically. Starting with ChromaDB and the vault structure in parallel.\", \"tool_calls\": [{\"function\": {\"name\": \"terminal\"}}, {\"function\": {\"name\": \"terminal\"}}]}]", "source": "session_20260316_041405_7716a6.json", "collected_at": "2026-03-26T12:28:33.944105"}
